<doc id="54450" wikidata="Q224338" url="?curid=54450" title="Adams County">
<text>Adams County is the name of twelve counties in the United States. Most are named for one of two presidents, John Adams or his son, John Quincy Adams:

*Adams County, Colorado
*Adams County, Idaho 
*Adams County, Illinois 
*Adams County, Indiana 
*Adams County, Iowa 
*Adams County, Mississippi 
*Adams County, Nebraska 
*Adams County, North Dakota 
*Adams County, Ohio 
*Adams County, Pennsylvania 
*Adams County, Washington 
*Adams County, Wisconsin </text><links>
